1
00:00:00,020 --> 00:00:04,290
[Disclaimer: This series is entirely fictional
and solely for entertainment purposes

2
00:00:04,320 --> 00:00:08,450
with no association or reference
to any individuals, places, or events;

3
00:00:08,480 --> 00:00:12,390
there may be inappropriate behaviors
and vulgarity based on the character's persona;

4
00:00:12,420 --> 00:00:14,660
viewer discretion is advised]

5
00:00:16,420 --> 00:00:18,100
You saw the photo I sent you, right?

6
00:00:18,680 --> 00:00:19,870
They finally met each other.

7
00:00:20,090 --> 00:00:21,580
Did you know from the beginning

8
00:00:22,170 --> 00:00:24,370
that I wasn't your childhood sweetheart?

9
00:00:24,620 --> 00:00:26,080
And for Pitcha,

10
00:00:26,230 --> 00:00:28,170
he also didn't want to
help Itthi trick you,

11
00:00:28,450 --> 00:00:30,500
- but he just...
- You knew...

12
00:00:30,530 --> 00:00:33,120
that Pitcha knew about this?

13
00:00:34,720 --> 00:00:35,840
Let's accept that,

14
00:00:36,800 --> 00:00:37,800
up until now,

15
00:00:40,220 --> 00:00:42,200
our love was never real to begin with.

16
00:00:49,500 --> 00:00:51,580
Our fun time is over.

17
00:00:52,890 --> 00:00:55,380
Are you really in the mood for jokes,
right now, Pure?

18
00:00:55,800 --> 00:00:56,930
Actually,

19
00:00:57,600 --> 00:00:59,610
we are all part of this.

20
00:01:00,400 --> 00:01:02,070
All of this is because of me.

21
00:01:05,470 --> 00:01:07,370
I was too chicken to hit on Ritt,

22
00:01:09,220 --> 00:01:10,830
so I chose this method.

23
00:01:12,510 --> 00:01:14,810
And Ritt is really into you.

24
00:01:14,960 --> 00:01:15,960
This incident...

25
00:01:16,220 --> 00:01:17,980
Fooling each other...

26
00:01:18,010 --> 00:01:18,890
In the end,

27
00:01:19,300 --> 00:01:20,890
you can't avoid the truth anyway.

28
00:01:22,470 --> 00:01:24,289
A liar never brings anyone a happy ending,

29
00:01:25,120 --> 00:01:27,300
but it comes at the cost of trust,

30
00:01:27,370 --> 00:01:28,550
which is very hard to restore.

31
00:01:30,270 --> 00:01:31,620
I feel guilty

32
00:01:31,670 --> 00:01:34,600
for being part of this major lie.

33
00:01:41,130 --> 00:01:42,759
Then what should we do next?

34
00:01:43,460 --> 00:01:45,140
Does anyone have a good idea

35
00:01:45,200 --> 00:01:46,539
for Itthi?

36
00:01:50,180 --> 00:01:51,180
Making up with him!

37
00:01:51,440 --> 00:01:52,440
Ever heard the saying,

38
00:01:52,820 --> 00:01:54,289
"Persistence is key"?

39
00:01:54,770 --> 00:01:55,770
Right now,

40
00:01:55,990 --> 00:01:57,450
the only weapon you can use

41
00:01:57,570 --> 00:01:58,570
is to make up with him.

42
00:01:58,890 --> 00:01:59,960
Do whatever it takes

43
00:01:59,990 --> 00:02:01,810
to make him forgive you.

44
00:02:04,050 --> 00:02:05,280
How should I?

45
00:02:05,500 --> 00:02:08,389
You just need to try every possible way

46
00:02:08,500 --> 00:02:10,610
to make up with him.

47
00:02:12,900 --> 00:02:14,540
You know it so well.

48
00:02:14,680 --> 00:02:16,530
Experienced that a lot, huh?

49
00:02:16,860 --> 00:02:20,010
No, I just learned it from others.

50
00:02:21,070 --> 00:02:22,550
Let me tell you some tricks.

51
00:02:22,990 --> 00:02:24,770
If I'm mad at you one day,

52
00:02:24,829 --> 00:02:26,770
all you need to do is just smile at me.

53
00:02:27,050 --> 00:02:28,050
That's enough.

54
00:02:31,590 --> 00:02:33,860
Flirting with each other
like we're not even here, huh?

55
00:02:48,220 --> 00:02:52,270
♫Is it pure coincidence?♫

56
00:02:52,300 --> 00:02:56,360
♫Or is it destiny that decides?♫

57
00:02:56,390 --> 00:02:58,640
♫Is someone above
drawing all these lines?♫

58
00:02:58,670 --> 00:03:04,840
♫Or playing matchmaker in disguise?♫

59
00:03:04,870 --> 00:03:09,230
♫What if the stars shift in their place♫

60
00:03:09,260 --> 00:03:12,640
♫Slightly out of line,♫

61
00:03:13,500 --> 00:03:17,190
♫Will our orbits still align?♫

62
00:03:17,220 --> 00:03:21,530
♫Try answering if your world
will cross with mine♫

63
00:03:21,560 --> 00:03:25,610
♫Though the destiny between us
is differently defined♫

64
00:03:25,630 --> 00:03:31,150
♫And I believe our love has power♫

65
00:03:31,170 --> 00:03:34,970
♫I believe the love of us♫

66
00:03:35,000 --> 00:03:44,380
♫Will realign the stars back to the line
where they should be♫

67
00:03:47,500 --> 00:03:48,500
Are you Ritt?

68
00:03:50,860 --> 00:03:51,579
Yes.

69
00:03:51,680 --> 00:03:52,610
Here are your flowers.

70
00:03:53,680 --> 00:03:55,030
He left this message for you, saying,

71
00:03:55,450 --> 00:03:56,280
"I'm so sorry."

72
00:03:59,750 --> 00:04:00,350
Sorry.

73
00:04:01,110 --> 00:04:01,810
Right.

74
00:04:06,680 --> 00:04:09,380
[From Itthi]

75
00:04:21,200 --> 00:04:22,990
- Hey.
- Whoa.

76
00:04:23,190 --> 00:04:24,670
So damn cute.

77
00:05:15,690 --> 00:05:21,510
[Please forgive me]

78
00:05:57,659 --> 00:06:01,080
[I'm so sorry]

79
00:06:06,280 --> 00:06:08,720
[I'm so sorry]

80
00:06:28,390 --> 00:06:30,910
Seriously, none of them worked?

81
00:06:33,320 --> 00:06:35,380
No response from him at all.

82
00:06:41,390 --> 00:06:42,210
Let's do it this way.

83
00:06:43,200 --> 00:06:44,480
Pitcha and I

84
00:06:45,060 --> 00:06:46,350
will be the frontmen for you.

85
00:06:47,880 --> 00:06:48,940
At least,

86
00:06:49,180 --> 00:06:50,340
I'm his close friend.

87
00:06:51,500 --> 00:06:53,040
No matter how badly he throws a fit

88
00:06:53,110 --> 00:06:54,270
or gets mad at me,

89
00:06:54,760 --> 00:06:56,190
our friendship can act as a shield.

90
00:06:58,110 --> 00:06:59,230
And you.

91
00:07:00,340 --> 00:07:03,820
You're enough of a stranger for Ritt
to mind his manners.

92
00:07:04,650 --> 00:07:06,410
Out of everyone here, I think

93
00:07:07,520 --> 00:07:09,170
Ritt might listen to you the most.

94
00:07:19,860 --> 00:07:21,600
Are you sure he'll get over it?

95
00:07:22,110 --> 00:07:23,500
We should try.

96
00:07:56,920 --> 00:07:57,920
Hello.

97
00:07:58,200 --> 00:07:59,200
It's me, Pitcha.

98
00:08:00,210 --> 00:08:01,990
I'm at your condo

99
00:08:03,180 --> 00:08:04,450
to accept your apology

100
00:08:05,210 --> 00:08:06,590
for pretending to be me.

101
00:08:40,370 --> 00:08:41,370
I knew it.

102
00:08:42,020 --> 00:08:43,110
This was your plan.

103
00:08:44,000 --> 00:08:45,000
No.

104
00:08:45,210 --> 00:08:46,290
I'm here to keep him company.

105
00:08:48,400 --> 00:08:49,600
I'm here to apologize

106
00:08:50,260 --> 00:08:51,760
and accept your apology.

107
00:08:53,450 --> 00:08:54,910
I have a hand in that.

108
00:08:55,660 --> 00:08:57,810
If I hadn't helped Itthi deceive you,

109
00:08:58,370 --> 00:09:00,210
you might not have ended up

110
00:09:01,910 --> 00:09:03,030
feeling like a joke.

111
00:09:05,980 --> 00:09:06,980
I understand you,

112
00:09:07,730 --> 00:09:09,130
and I really want to say sorry.

113
00:09:15,550 --> 00:09:17,640
I think we should sit first, shall we?

114
00:09:17,920 --> 00:09:20,170
If not, we're going to be standing here
talking for a long time.

115
00:09:36,080 --> 00:09:37,200
To be honest, Ritt,

116
00:09:38,230 --> 00:09:39,500
think twice.

117
00:09:40,320 --> 00:09:42,620
You started all of this yourself

118
00:09:43,080 --> 00:09:44,580
because you wanted to be close
to Itthi so much

119
00:09:45,190 --> 00:09:48,510
that you forgot
you had used dishonest means

120
00:09:51,410 --> 00:09:53,510
and started making up stories
to deceive him.

121
00:09:54,040 --> 00:09:55,620
If he did what you did,

122
00:09:55,990 --> 00:09:57,110
it's fair game, isn't it?

123
00:09:58,750 --> 00:10:01,100
It's not fair for you to be mad at him.

124
00:10:02,430 --> 00:10:03,430
If you rob a thief,

125
00:10:04,350 --> 00:10:05,840
you become a thief.

126
00:10:11,100 --> 00:10:12,530
I'm so sorry

127
00:10:13,340 --> 00:10:14,710
that I impersonated you.

128
00:10:16,300 --> 00:10:17,610
It was my fault

129
00:10:17,970 --> 00:10:18,970
for drinking too much

130
00:10:20,160 --> 00:10:22,290
and being impulsive.

131
00:10:25,060 --> 00:10:26,200
But I think it was deliberate.

132
00:10:29,120 --> 00:10:31,180
You were planning
to get him no matter what.

133
00:10:31,540 --> 00:10:32,800
That's why you used that method.

134
00:10:33,970 --> 00:10:35,060
Yeah! It was my fault.

135
00:10:35,620 --> 00:10:36,620
All of it started because of me.

136
00:10:37,200 --> 00:10:38,100
I was bad.

137
00:10:38,450 --> 00:10:39,390
I was wrong.

138
00:10:39,720 --> 00:10:40,800
Is this what you want?!

139
00:10:41,640 --> 00:10:42,600
I deserve

140
00:10:42,760 --> 00:10:44,210
to be like this.

141
00:10:44,700 --> 00:10:45,430
Okay?

142
00:10:51,550 --> 00:10:52,710
Uh... I think

143
00:10:52,890 --> 00:10:54,310
you and Itthi

144
00:10:55,090 --> 00:10:56,480
actually have the same purpose.

145
00:10:57,340 --> 00:10:58,990
You just liked each other,

146
00:10:59,510 --> 00:11:02,580
but no one was brave enough
to disclose their true feelings

147
00:11:03,600 --> 00:11:05,110
and ended up using the same method.

148
00:11:05,810 --> 00:11:07,300
That's why everything
turned out like this.

149
00:11:11,480 --> 00:11:13,490
So it's you who needs
to make up with Itthi.

150
00:11:14,100 --> 00:11:15,400
Say sorry to him

151
00:11:16,030 --> 00:11:17,580
and clear things up.

152
00:11:21,100 --> 00:11:22,600
There are over a billion people
in this world,

153
00:11:23,360 --> 00:11:25,700
but not many of them

154
00:11:26,260 --> 00:11:27,670
can make you feel this way.

155
00:11:29,760 --> 00:11:32,020
Fate brought two people together.

156
00:11:35,070 --> 00:11:36,920
Coincidences don't usually happen.

157
00:11:38,010 --> 00:11:39,320
If you still have feelings for him,

158
00:11:40,210 --> 00:11:41,600
just don't let those mistakes

159
00:11:42,200 --> 00:11:45,910
destroy what fate has destined for you.

160
00:11:50,040 --> 00:11:51,040
I'm positive that

161
00:11:51,780 --> 00:11:53,180
Itthi loves you so much

162
00:11:54,600 --> 00:11:56,320
that he can forgive you no matter what.

163
00:11:58,730 --> 00:11:59,920
Just try asking yourself

164
00:12:01,470 --> 00:12:03,090
if you love Itthi enough

165
00:12:03,410 --> 00:12:04,630
to forgive both him

166
00:12:05,090 --> 00:12:06,410
and yourself.

167
00:12:29,090 --> 00:12:31,210
If you want to keep him safe,

168
00:12:32,090 --> 00:12:33,310
give me one million baht.

169
00:12:34,710 --> 00:12:36,000
Not too much, is it?

170
00:12:37,920 --> 00:12:39,380
If I don't receive the money

171
00:12:40,430 --> 00:12:41,810
before midnight,

172
00:12:44,140 --> 00:12:45,420
I can't guarantee

173
00:12:46,850 --> 00:12:48,520
what will happen

174
00:12:49,120 --> 00:12:51,000
to your beloved boyfriend.

175
00:13:05,460 --> 00:13:06,400
Who are you?

176
00:13:07,050 --> 00:13:08,080
What have you done to Ritt?

177
00:13:16,690 --> 00:13:20,870
If I don't see any cash
at the meeting point before midnight,

178
00:13:20,900 --> 00:13:24,960
I can't guarantee what will happen
to your beloved boyfriend.

179
00:13:34,140 --> 00:13:34,780
Oh,

180
00:13:34,910 --> 00:13:36,070
Itthi.

181
00:13:36,130 --> 00:13:38,000
Why are you in such a rush, huh?

182
00:13:38,160 --> 00:13:39,420
Yeah, what happened?

183
00:13:40,170 --> 00:13:41,090
Tell me.

184
00:13:46,840 --> 00:13:47,720
Okay.

185
00:13:48,500 --> 00:13:50,550
As your best friend,
I feel like I've done my job

186
00:13:50,570 --> 00:13:52,450
of bringing you back to your senses.

187
00:13:53,450 --> 00:13:54,790
So, after this, it's up to you

188
00:13:55,180 --> 00:13:56,120
what you want to do next.

189
00:13:57,030 --> 00:14:00,010
Actually, we also need to apologize to you

190
00:14:00,420 --> 00:14:02,330
for playing along with Itthi.

191
00:14:02,620 --> 00:14:03,530
I'm sorry.

192
00:14:04,650 --> 00:14:08,730
Yeah, I'm sorry, Ritt.

193
00:14:16,910 --> 00:14:18,310
What is he going to do again?

194
00:14:20,940 --> 00:14:23,890
Ritt was taken hostage.
I'm on my way to help him.

195
00:14:25,620 --> 00:14:29,370
[View map]

196
00:14:29,550 --> 00:14:30,130
Now what?

197
00:14:31,160 --> 00:14:31,900
I got it.

198
00:14:31,990 --> 00:14:33,570
He wanted us to follow the map

199
00:14:33,960 --> 00:14:35,670
and set up a surprise reconciliation
for him, for sure.

200
00:14:36,810 --> 00:14:38,480
It's about to get better.

201
00:14:38,630 --> 00:14:40,910
Still using a make-up story plan, huh?

202
00:14:42,030 --> 00:14:43,700
Let's use a counterplot.

203
00:14:47,660 --> 00:14:48,890
Where are you, Itthi?

204
00:14:49,280 --> 00:14:51,890
I'm heading to the location he sent me.

205
00:14:53,780 --> 00:14:54,780
Are you?

206
00:14:55,740 --> 00:14:57,790
Who sent you, huh?

207
00:14:59,390 --> 00:15:00,480
I don't know either.

208
00:15:00,720 --> 00:15:02,180
He sent me a message.

209
00:15:02,400 --> 00:15:03,510
I'll send it to you.

210
00:15:03,690 --> 00:15:05,340
That's it. I have to go.

211
00:15:08,060 --> 00:15:09,200
Nice acting, though.

212
00:15:09,570 --> 00:15:11,210
His voice is so serious.

213
00:15:11,640 --> 00:15:14,300
He must have secretly taken
an acting course.

214
00:15:17,090 --> 00:15:18,010
Aha.

215
00:15:18,500 --> 00:15:22,000
Look, he made up evidence
to make it look convincing.

216
00:15:34,030 --> 00:15:35,560
Why does the number look familiar, though?

217
00:15:36,420 --> 00:15:37,540
How?

218
00:16:08,560 --> 00:16:09,800
Look who's here.

219
00:16:10,590 --> 00:16:11,800
Ritt's sweetheart.

220
00:16:12,590 --> 00:16:14,530
A perfect, charming man.

221
00:16:16,470 --> 00:16:17,470
Where is Ritt?

222
00:16:18,340 --> 00:16:19,340
What have you done to him?

223
00:16:20,230 --> 00:16:21,410
Nothing,

224
00:16:22,170 --> 00:16:24,780
I haven't done anything
to your beloved boyfriend.

225
00:16:27,350 --> 00:16:28,350
So what do you want?!

226
00:16:30,310 --> 00:16:32,870
I want what's in your hand.

227
00:16:33,220 --> 00:16:34,840
Place it there

228
00:16:34,870 --> 00:16:36,390
and walk back to your car.

229
00:16:37,180 --> 00:16:38,580
Your beloved boyfriend

230
00:16:38,910 --> 00:16:40,220
will wait for you there

231
00:16:40,860 --> 00:16:42,620
right after I get what I want.

232
00:16:43,280 --> 00:16:44,280
How can I know

233
00:16:44,540 --> 00:16:45,970
that you're not playing dirty?

234
00:16:46,610 --> 00:16:48,070
Right?

235
00:16:48,500 --> 00:16:49,800
How can I know

236
00:16:50,720 --> 00:16:52,320
if money is in that bag?

237
00:16:58,500 --> 00:16:59,900
Place it there

238
00:17:01,510 --> 00:17:04,210
and walk back to your beloved boyfriend.

239
00:17:05,180 --> 00:17:06,180
No.

240
00:17:06,750 --> 00:17:08,460
Let me see Ritt first.

241
00:17:09,609 --> 00:17:11,510
You think you can still bargain
with me, huh?

242
00:17:12,160 --> 00:17:14,910
You're not worried about your lover at all,

243
00:17:14,940 --> 00:17:15,720
are you?

244
00:17:17,770 --> 00:17:19,790
Do you think I'm so stupid
that I believe you?

245
00:17:21,310 --> 00:17:22,310
Take Ritt out!

246
00:17:23,690 --> 00:17:24,690
Where is Ritt?!!

247
00:17:36,920 --> 00:17:37,490
Ouch!

248
00:17:50,640 --> 00:17:51,410
Let go of me.

249
00:17:51,990 --> 00:17:52,580
No!

250
00:17:57,410 --> 00:17:58,480
I told you to let go of me.

251
00:17:59,320 --> 00:18:01,000
Tell me. Where is Ritt?!!

252
00:18:04,010 --> 00:18:05,180
I said, "Where is Ritt?"

253
00:18:08,100 --> 00:18:09,000
Let go of me!

254
00:18:10,250 --> 00:18:11,870
Who are you, though?

255
00:18:18,330 --> 00:18:18,780
Itthi!

256
00:18:18,850 --> 00:18:19,340
Itthi.

257
00:18:21,730 --> 00:18:22,390
Ritt.

258
00:18:25,540 --> 00:18:26,900
Are you okay, Ritt?

259
00:18:30,220 --> 00:18:31,720
Let him go right now!

260
00:18:32,250 --> 00:18:33,990
Tell me what you want!

261
00:18:34,300 --> 00:18:35,950
You don't have to do this!

262
00:18:37,190 --> 00:18:38,490
All of you, get out of here.

263
00:18:39,050 --> 00:18:39,700
Or else,

264
00:18:40,110 --> 00:18:41,720
I'm stabbing him to death here!

265
00:18:41,760 --> 00:18:42,520
Hey!

266
00:18:42,700 --> 00:18:43,860
Don't you dare!!

267
00:18:44,170 --> 00:18:45,430
Why are you doing this?!

268
00:18:45,500 --> 00:18:46,620
What on earth do you want?!

269
00:18:48,830 --> 00:18:49,780
You know?

270
00:18:50,410 --> 00:18:52,280
My life ended up like this

271
00:18:53,070 --> 00:18:54,880
because of your stupid prophecies.

272
00:18:56,310 --> 00:18:57,310
You said it was going to be fine.

273
00:18:58,130 --> 00:18:58,880
Fine?

274
00:18:59,200 --> 00:19:00,520
I just believed you!

275
00:19:01,150 --> 00:19:03,200
My family went bankrupt!

276
00:19:03,540 --> 00:19:05,500
Wasn't that because
of your persuasive words?

277
00:19:07,500 --> 00:19:08,600
And this

278
00:19:09,490 --> 00:19:11,010
is the price you have to pay

279
00:19:11,480 --> 00:19:14,300
for fucking up my life like this!!

280
00:19:14,440 --> 00:19:15,180
Stop it.

281
00:19:16,520 --> 00:19:17,610
Hold on.

282
00:19:18,730 --> 00:19:20,050
Let's calm down and talk it out.

283
00:19:20,470 --> 00:19:21,800
Put your weapon down.

284
00:19:22,020 --> 00:19:23,020
Officers,

285
00:19:23,260 --> 00:19:23,880
well...

286
00:19:24,970 --> 00:19:25,890
The two of us

287
00:19:26,040 --> 00:19:27,350
are friends, officers.

288
00:19:27,820 --> 00:19:29,190
Hey, dude.

289
00:19:30,100 --> 00:19:31,190
Can't you remember me?

290
00:19:31,260 --> 00:19:32,560
We're friends.

291
00:19:33,160 --> 00:19:34,200
Think about it.

292
00:19:36,110 --> 00:19:37,460
This knife is fake.

293
00:19:37,490 --> 00:19:38,180
Calm down.

294
00:19:39,000 --> 00:19:40,170
Drop your weapon.

295
00:19:41,050 --> 00:19:42,010
Officers,

296
00:19:42,300 --> 00:19:43,190
this is

297
00:19:43,590 --> 00:19:44,950
just a fake knife.

298
00:19:45,650 --> 00:19:46,580
It's fake.

299
00:19:46,700 --> 00:19:47,750
If you don't believe me...

300
00:19:47,770 --> 00:19:48,720
I can show you.

301
00:19:48,880 --> 00:19:49,870
Hey, calm down.

302
00:19:50,250 --> 00:19:51,390
See?

303
00:19:52,820 --> 00:19:53,360
Look.

304
00:19:54,350 --> 00:19:55,350
Can you see it?

305
00:19:55,810 --> 00:19:56,810
It's fake.

306
00:19:57,790 --> 00:19:58,830
Do you believe me now?

307
00:19:58,930 --> 00:19:59,930
It's fake.

308
00:20:00,320 --> 00:20:01,570
Arrest him, officers!

309
00:20:01,780 --> 00:20:02,780
It's this guy!

310
00:20:03,430 --> 00:20:05,310
He extorted me, too!

311
00:20:05,630 --> 00:20:07,490
Also, he made a fake video to trick us

312
00:20:08,000 --> 00:20:09,060
out of our money.

313
00:20:09,780 --> 00:20:10,390
Hey,

314
00:20:11,100 --> 00:20:12,760
drop the knife!

315
00:20:13,330 --> 00:20:14,330
Drop it!

316
00:20:15,190 --> 00:20:16,090
Major, charge!

317
00:20:19,700 --> 00:20:21,290
This is actually fake, sir.

318
00:20:21,590 --> 00:20:22,380
Let's go to the police station.

319
00:20:22,870 --> 00:20:23,920
I don't want to.

320
00:20:24,850 --> 00:20:26,290
Before going to the police station,

321
00:20:26,750 --> 00:20:28,110
let's go to the hospital first.

322
00:20:28,770 --> 00:20:29,380
Go.

323
00:20:47,120 --> 00:20:48,460
Why are you this hotheaded?

324
00:20:48,740 --> 00:20:49,260
Huh, Itthi?

325
00:20:50,320 --> 00:20:52,810
It isn't just love that makes him blind.

326
00:20:53,200 --> 00:20:56,220
How do you not know it's an AI video, huh?

327
00:20:59,910 --> 00:21:00,910
I was just worried about him.

328
00:21:02,620 --> 00:21:03,810
What do you expect me to do?

329
00:21:04,540 --> 00:21:05,360
Fine.

330
00:21:06,940 --> 00:21:08,990
Your hand is injured.
Does it hurt?

331
00:21:12,820 --> 00:21:13,520
Well.

332
00:21:14,100 --> 00:21:14,720
Alright.

333
00:21:15,510 --> 00:21:18,110
I'm handing over this responsibility
to take care of you to Ritt.

334
00:21:19,100 --> 00:21:20,500
Hey, I'm okay.

335
00:21:24,890 --> 00:21:25,790
No problem.

336
00:21:32,410 --> 00:21:33,800
As long as you are fine.

337
00:21:42,260 --> 00:21:43,260
Are you worried about me?

338
00:21:47,590 --> 00:21:48,300
Ouch!

339
00:21:50,010 --> 00:21:50,620
That hurts.

340
00:21:52,190 --> 00:21:53,190
Be gentle.

341
00:21:56,050 --> 00:21:56,920
There you go.

342
00:21:57,600 --> 00:21:59,510
This is the consequence of being gullible

343
00:22:00,390 --> 00:22:02,600
and not using
any of your critical thinking skills.

344
00:22:02,630 --> 00:22:03,280
See?!

345
00:22:04,600 --> 00:22:06,120
I was worried about you, though.

346
00:22:08,500 --> 00:22:10,090
Also, that AI video

347
00:22:10,900 --> 00:22:12,320
looked so real.

348
00:22:14,020 --> 00:22:16,080
Since you can't distinguish

349
00:22:16,560 --> 00:22:17,620
between real and fake,

350
00:22:18,020 --> 00:22:19,140
you deserve it.

351
00:22:21,800 --> 00:22:22,800
Look at you.

352
00:22:25,050 --> 00:22:26,280
I got hurt

353
00:22:26,440 --> 00:22:27,930
because I was worried about you.

354
00:22:30,020 --> 00:22:32,610
Instead of appreciating it,
you just added insult to injury.

355
00:22:36,030 --> 00:22:37,670
Thank you for your care.

356
00:22:44,800 --> 00:22:45,800
That's all for now.

357
00:22:47,100 --> 00:22:49,360
Tomorrow, if it gets worse,

358
00:22:49,920 --> 00:22:52,030
just let the doctor take a look at it.

359
00:22:58,500 --> 00:23:00,080
Can Master Ritt look at it instead?

360
00:23:02,250 --> 00:23:03,250
Still joking, huh?

361
00:23:33,740 --> 00:23:35,890
If getting hurt makes you forgive me,

362
00:23:36,980 --> 00:23:38,210
it's quite worth it.

363
00:23:43,300 --> 00:23:44,960
At least, I know

364
00:23:45,900 --> 00:23:47,730
how much you care about me.

365
00:23:59,010 --> 00:24:00,500
Let's make up soon,

366
00:24:01,390 --> 00:24:02,860
so we can get back to how we were.

367
00:24:05,220 --> 00:24:06,220
"How we were"?

368
00:24:10,820 --> 00:24:11,820
What do you mean by that?

369
00:24:13,360 --> 00:24:14,360
- Well...
- Don't forget...

370
00:24:15,480 --> 00:24:16,570
that I'm not your real sweetheart.

371
00:24:18,400 --> 00:24:20,010
Your childhood sweetheart

372
00:24:20,120 --> 00:24:21,120
is Pitcha.

373
00:24:22,560 --> 00:24:23,690
I was just impersonating him

374
00:24:25,110 --> 00:24:26,330
and playing along,

375
00:24:26,600 --> 00:24:27,900
not realizing I'd fallen for your trick.

376
00:24:31,930 --> 00:24:32,580
Whoa,

377
00:24:33,730 --> 00:24:34,800
that was a lot.

378
00:24:37,080 --> 00:24:38,080
I just found out

379
00:24:38,910 --> 00:24:40,420
that you're quick to get mad
but slow to forgive.

380
00:24:42,040 --> 00:24:42,940
Honestly,

381
00:24:45,110 --> 00:24:46,650
I'm not sure anymore

382
00:24:47,210 --> 00:24:49,330
what's joking or what's serious,

383
00:24:50,780 --> 00:24:52,490
what your true feelings are,

384
00:24:54,010 --> 00:24:55,480
and what my own feelings are.

385
00:25:00,340 --> 00:25:01,410
If so...

386
00:25:03,000 --> 00:25:04,700
I also want to know

387
00:25:05,230 --> 00:25:07,440
about the feelings of that boy,

388
00:25:08,910 --> 00:25:11,860
who secretly took a picture of me
while I was practicing swimming

389
00:25:14,170 --> 00:25:16,480
and set it as his phone wallpaper.

390
00:25:19,950 --> 00:25:22,290
What were the feelings of that boy?

391
00:26:02,750 --> 00:26:04,440
Coach, I'm gonna head out now.

392
00:26:04,640 --> 00:26:05,700
- Bye.
- Bye now.

393
00:26:05,840 --> 00:26:07,910
Oh! Itthiphumi,
are you forgetting your phone?

394
00:26:08,160 --> 00:26:09,510
Uh... My phone is right here.

395
00:26:09,750 --> 00:26:11,520
Hey, double-check it.

396
00:26:12,140 --> 00:26:13,140
You sure this isn't yours?

397
00:26:21,730 --> 00:26:24,680
Excuse me, that's my phone.

398
00:26:34,950 --> 00:26:35,980
You remember that!

399
00:26:39,190 --> 00:26:40,000
Of course.

400
00:26:41,690 --> 00:26:42,960
I remember it clearly.

401
00:26:43,520 --> 00:26:44,520
But why...

402
00:26:50,430 --> 00:26:51,330
Okay.

403
00:26:53,360 --> 00:26:55,500
That must have been another
funny thing for you.

404
00:26:59,040 --> 00:27:00,110
I shouldn't have mentioned that.

405
00:27:01,450 --> 00:27:02,780
It almost went well.

406
00:27:05,950 --> 00:27:07,490
Be honest.

407
00:27:08,390 --> 00:27:09,580
Does what I did

408
00:27:11,100 --> 00:27:13,210
seem so funny to you?

409
00:27:15,600 --> 00:27:18,310
Besides being someone you use
to satisfy your sexual needs

410
00:27:19,600 --> 00:27:20,510
and a clown,

411
00:27:22,270 --> 00:27:23,390
what else am I to you?

412
00:27:27,130 --> 00:27:28,370
You're the one I love.

413
00:27:30,740 --> 00:27:32,910
Is this what you did to the one you love?

414
00:27:34,900 --> 00:27:36,970
What about your impersonation of Pitcha,

415
00:27:37,910 --> 00:27:39,620
and trying to get close to me?

416
00:27:40,710 --> 00:27:42,440
Isn't that because you love me?

417
00:27:47,220 --> 00:27:48,460
I'm not sure

418
00:27:49,760 --> 00:27:51,450
what I'm actually feeling either.

419
00:27:55,730 --> 00:27:57,570
Should we just spend time...

420
00:27:57,730 --> 00:28:00,790
figuring out our feelings?

421
00:28:02,450 --> 00:28:03,480
So that we can see

422
00:28:04,470 --> 00:28:05,470
if it should be over

423
00:28:06,000 --> 00:28:07,000
between us

424
00:28:09,300 --> 00:28:11,000
or if there's still a way forward.

425
00:28:16,800 --> 00:28:18,120
I don't want it this way.

426
00:28:20,010 --> 00:28:22,110
Come on, let me hug you.

427
00:29:08,760 --> 00:29:09,610
Nervous?

428
00:29:10,020 --> 00:29:11,900
Of course. Look at mine.

429
00:29:18,690 --> 00:29:19,460
Hey, Noah.

430
00:29:19,910 --> 00:29:21,080
I don't think you're gonna make it.

431
00:29:22,990 --> 00:29:24,160
I think so.

432
00:29:24,990 --> 00:29:25,680
Should we go home?

433
00:29:27,700 --> 00:29:29,070
You can do it. You can do it.

434
00:29:29,110 --> 00:29:30,010
Hey, it's your turn.

435
00:29:30,810 --> 00:29:31,560
Ritt,

436
00:29:32,150 --> 00:29:33,300
your turn.

437
00:29:37,990 --> 00:29:39,350
I should go home.

438
00:29:41,330 --> 00:29:43,470
Every stone we see as solid

439
00:29:43,630 --> 00:29:44,520
and lifeless

440
00:29:45,150 --> 00:29:47,790
is actually a diary of time,

441
00:29:47,910 --> 00:29:48,910
energy,

442
00:29:49,450 --> 00:29:50,280
stories,

443
00:29:50,890 --> 00:29:53,880
and a bridge between people and living space.

444
00:29:54,040 --> 00:29:55,770
This design

445
00:29:55,800 --> 00:29:58,090
was based on the beliefs of various cultures,

446
00:29:58,160 --> 00:30:00,310
as you can see in every detail.

447
00:30:00,800 --> 00:30:04,520
In Chinese culture, stones are believed
to enhance elemental energy.

448
00:30:04,810 --> 00:30:08,820
In Thai culture, they are regarded
as having protective properties.

449
00:30:09,470 --> 00:30:11,040
In the West,

450
00:30:11,060 --> 00:30:15,160
stones are often seen
as conductors of energy and frequencies.

451
00:30:15,380 --> 00:30:19,320
I'm not saying that we should let these stones
dictate our lives or our future.

452
00:30:19,580 --> 00:30:20,990
But I'll use them

453
00:30:21,030 --> 00:30:23,800
to help evoke various kinds of feelings.

454
00:30:23,950 --> 00:30:26,210
For example, some of them provide
a sense of stability,

455
00:30:26,850 --> 00:30:28,860
while some provide a sense of warmth.

456
00:30:29,160 --> 00:30:31,990
And placing them in certain positions
helps us find clarity

457
00:30:32,220 --> 00:30:34,090
in things we may have overlooked.

458
00:30:34,350 --> 00:30:38,320
I believe that placing
these stones in different positions

459
00:30:38,470 --> 00:30:41,880
is like giving our hearts to someone.

460
00:30:44,890 --> 00:30:47,200
If we place it in the right place,

461
00:30:47,540 --> 00:30:49,520
it'll build inner stability

462
00:30:50,240 --> 00:30:51,880
and make us realize

463
00:30:52,140 --> 00:30:54,610
where our hearts should be

464
00:30:54,640 --> 00:30:57,320
or with whom they will bloom.

465
00:30:57,840 --> 00:30:59,060
Thank you so much.

466
00:31:03,990 --> 00:31:05,180
Good job, Ritt.

467
00:31:05,880 --> 00:31:08,390
Throughout the past semester,

468
00:31:08,720 --> 00:31:10,560
I've seen the determination

469
00:31:10,600 --> 00:31:12,870
and devotion you put into this work.

470
00:31:13,710 --> 00:31:14,990
And the outcome

471
00:31:15,060 --> 00:31:16,930
is so satisfying!

472
00:31:19,340 --> 00:31:22,420
I really love the way you
drew from different beliefs

473
00:31:22,480 --> 00:31:24,530
to rationalize architectural design.

474
00:31:24,660 --> 00:31:27,130
And you gave
logical explanations for many things

475
00:31:27,160 --> 00:31:29,010
people consider superstitions.

476
00:31:29,410 --> 00:31:32,600
If he doesn't have any plans after graduating yet,
I'd like him to work with me.

477
00:31:33,340 --> 00:31:34,280
Yes, sure.

478
00:31:40,050 --> 00:31:40,960
Why is it taking him so long?

479
00:31:41,450 --> 00:31:42,530
Yeah.

480
00:31:45,710 --> 00:31:46,830
How was it going?

481
00:31:47,650 --> 00:31:48,740
Yeah, how was it?

482
00:31:49,210 --> 00:31:50,210
Not bad.

483
00:31:50,820 --> 00:31:52,000
The professor said,

484
00:31:53,050 --> 00:31:54,240
"Brilliant!"

485
00:31:54,590 --> 00:31:56,080
- Gosh!
- Whoa.

486
00:31:56,850 --> 00:31:58,340
Even better than that guy?

487
00:31:58,740 --> 00:31:59,700
They might let everyone pass.

488
00:32:00,910 --> 00:32:01,910
I'm rooting for you.

489
00:32:02,560 --> 00:32:03,130
Jeez,

490
00:32:03,430 --> 00:32:04,430
look at yours

491
00:32:04,470 --> 00:32:05,470
and look at mine.

492
00:32:06,530 --> 00:32:07,730
Mine might have a chance,

493
00:32:08,850 --> 00:32:10,210
but yours probably won't make it.

494
00:32:11,260 --> 00:32:12,470
Stop talking nonsense!

495
00:32:12,540 --> 00:32:13,330
Go away!

496
00:32:13,940 --> 00:32:14,680
I'll catch you later.

497
00:32:14,810 --> 00:32:15,610
Good luck.

498
00:32:24,350 --> 00:32:25,970
Grandpa isn't doing well.

499
00:32:26,310 --> 00:32:28,200
He wants to see you.

500
00:32:34,580 --> 00:32:35,850
Ready? Let's do it together.

501
00:32:35,910 --> 00:32:38,330
Five, six, seven, eight.

502
00:32:38,740 --> 00:32:42,160
♫I told you that maybe not yet♫

503
00:32:42,280 --> 00:32:44,320
♫Maybe not yet♫

504
00:32:44,690 --> 00:32:48,520
♫Maybe my feelings can't be contained♫

505
00:32:49,070 --> 00:32:50,160
One, two.

506
00:32:50,690 --> 00:32:52,890
♫My heart says♫

507
00:32:52,930 --> 00:32:54,630
♫I love you♫

508
00:32:54,820 --> 00:32:58,310
♫I don't know how to stop it♫

509
00:32:59,330 --> 00:33:00,010
Okay.

510
00:33:00,140 --> 00:33:02,490
Let's give it a try together.

511
00:33:03,040 --> 00:33:03,760
Come on.

512
00:33:04,620 --> 00:33:06,090
Three, four.

513
00:33:06,230 --> 00:33:09,990
I told you that maybe not yet...

514
00:33:10,410 --> 00:33:11,680
Maybe not yet.

515
00:33:12,310 --> 00:33:13,390
Pitcha,

516
00:33:13,700 --> 00:33:15,190
did you come to watch us practice?

517
00:33:15,760 --> 00:33:16,490
Yeah.

518
00:33:17,800 --> 00:33:18,600
Well...

519
00:33:18,720 --> 00:33:20,910
I'm here to see how everyone is doing.

520
00:33:22,850 --> 00:33:23,620
Also...

521
00:33:25,390 --> 00:33:26,830
I have something to tell you.

522
00:33:32,360 --> 00:33:33,360
Well...

523
00:33:33,940 --> 00:33:35,820
I'm going back to Korea for an audition

524
00:33:36,270 --> 00:33:37,750
at JJV Agency again.

525
00:33:40,940 --> 00:33:44,950
You're about to
make your dream come true, right?

526
00:33:46,080 --> 00:33:47,600
The agency has given me this opportunity,

527
00:33:48,240 --> 00:33:49,660
so I'd like to give it another try.

528
00:33:50,110 --> 00:33:52,310
That means you won't be with us

529
00:33:52,350 --> 00:33:54,760
on the competition day, right?

530
00:33:55,240 --> 00:33:58,070
Even though you won't be there that day,

531
00:33:58,230 --> 00:34:00,480
we'll dance our hearts out.

532
00:34:00,800 --> 00:34:03,680
And we'll send you
the video of us receiving the award.

533
00:34:05,020 --> 00:34:06,020
Sure.

534
00:34:07,500 --> 00:34:09,489
I'm looking forward
to seeing your success, guys.

535
00:34:10,440 --> 00:34:12,780
And I'll be cheering you on from Korea.

536
00:34:15,139 --> 00:34:17,320
No matter what path you choose,

537
00:34:17,400 --> 00:34:20,380
we hope it paves the way to your dreams.

538
00:34:24,510 --> 00:34:25,389
Thank you so much.

539
00:34:26,800 --> 00:34:29,620
Let's send Pitcha some support, shall we?

540
00:34:35,409 --> 00:34:38,850
You can do it, Pitcha. You can do it.

541
00:34:38,880 --> 00:34:41,600
You can do it, Pitcha. You can do it.

542
00:34:46,840 --> 00:34:49,190
[Magic Move]

543
00:35:04,940 --> 00:35:06,530
Who came, hmm?

544
00:35:07,920 --> 00:35:09,040
It's Ritt, Grandpa.

545
00:35:09,930 --> 00:35:11,150
Oh, Ritt.

546
00:35:12,850 --> 00:35:14,530
How could you be here?

547
00:35:14,880 --> 00:35:16,700
You two already got back together,

548
00:35:17,010 --> 00:35:17,700
right?

549
00:35:18,350 --> 00:35:19,610
How are you, Grandpa?

550
00:35:21,690 --> 00:35:23,120
Just an elderly thing.

551
00:35:23,760 --> 00:35:27,440
My battery life is almost worn out.

552
00:35:27,770 --> 00:35:29,540
I don't know how long I can live.

553
00:35:29,600 --> 00:35:30,600
Hey, Ritt.

554
00:35:30,760 --> 00:35:31,600
Did you bring...

555
00:35:31,630 --> 00:35:34,000
the prophecy stones with you?

556
00:35:34,280 --> 00:35:36,190
Come read my fortune

557
00:35:36,240 --> 00:35:38,040
to see how long I can live.

558
00:35:38,080 --> 00:35:39,080
Hey!

559
00:35:39,210 --> 00:35:41,350
You're talking nonsense.

560
00:35:43,890 --> 00:35:45,770
Haven't you gotten back together yet?

561
00:35:45,810 --> 00:35:47,220
Your faces look stern.

562
00:35:50,500 --> 00:35:52,230
Ritt and Itthi,

563
00:35:53,760 --> 00:35:57,000
you know how to love each other,

564
00:35:57,490 --> 00:36:00,800
but you also need to know
how to forgive each other.

565
00:36:01,320 --> 00:36:03,500
It's okay to have a fight
or be mad at each other.

566
00:36:05,560 --> 00:36:07,810
That's normal.

567
00:36:09,350 --> 00:36:10,610
But you need to learn

568
00:36:11,210 --> 00:36:15,240
to talk to reach an understanding,

569
00:36:16,230 --> 00:36:19,200
so you'll stay together for as long

570
00:36:19,750 --> 00:36:22,130
